videostream (2.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * V4L2 Device Discovery API: Automatic detection of cameras, encoders, and decoders
  * Auto-detect devices by capability - no more hardcoded /dev/videoX paths
  * New CLI command: videostream devices - list and filter V4L2 devices
  * Smart device grouping by bus_info to deduplicate multi-channel hardware
  * Filter flags: --cameras, --encoders, --decoders, --converters
  * DMA heap-backed USERPTR allocation for zero-copy pipelines
  * Real format enumeration via VIDIOC_ENUM_FMT (no more hardcoded lists)
  * Resolution enumeration via VIDIOC_ENUM_FRAMESIZES
  * Comprehensive Doxygen documentation with @since 2.2 annotations
  * Full Rust rustdoc with examples for docs.rs

 -- Sébastien Taylor <sebastien@au-zone.com>  Sat, 01 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000

videostream (2.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * VideoStream CLI: Modern Rust CLI with stream, record, receive, info, convert commands
  * V4L2 Codec Backend: Hardware encoder/decoder via V4L2 mem2mem API
  * VPU Decoder DMA Heap Support for zero-copy decode pipelines
  * Rust API Improvements: Rect type, Debug traits, #[non_exhaustive] enums
  * Fixed VPU decode latency (200ms → near-zero with KICK mode)
  * Fixed IPC deadlock and memory corruption bugs
  * Fixed stack smashing on aarch64 platforms
  * Resolved memory leaks and SonarCloud code quality issues

 -- Sébastien Taylor <sebastien@au-zone.com>  Sat, 04 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000

videostream (2.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: Python package namespace changed from deepview.videostream to videostream
